Buried in the tomb of Joseph of Arimathea.
Resurrected on the third day (Nisan 16).
Appears to disciples walking from Jerusalem.
Appears to apostles and disciples on a mountain.
Ascends to heaven on the 40th day after his resurrection.
Pours out holy spirit on the disciples at Pentecost.
Entrusted by Jesus to the care of the apostle John while at the torture stake.
Persisted in prayer in an upper room with the apostles and others after Jesus' ascension.
Present with the disciples when the holy spirit was poured out at Pentecost.
Assembles in an upper chamber with the apostles and his brothers persisting in prayer.

Writes the second letter of Peter.
